<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
<!--
  RE-ENABLED in v1.13.1-mlog012bp (X4 9.0 release compatibility).

  Vanilla 9.0 restructured order.move.recon.xml. The equivalent scan-clear
  point is now near line 1601, under a <do_else> block that fires when the
  police ship is clearing a scanned target (the scan revealed nothing
  actionable and we are releasing the halted target).

  Structure at the target site:

    <do_else>
      <debug_text text="'clearing %s %s %s'..."/>
      <do_if value="$localtarget.isclass.ship">                       (anchor)
        <do_if value="@$localtarget.pilot.$haltedby == ...">
          <set_value name="this.$police_cleared.{$localtarget}"       (we prepend our signal before this)
                     exact="player.age"/>
        </do_if>
        ...
      </do_if>
      ...
    </do_else>

  A second structurally similar site exists at line ~205 inside an
  interrupt/attack handler ("called to attack. clearing target"). To
  disambiguate we anchor on the sibling debug_text prefix in the parent
  do_else:

    - target site's debug_text starts with "'clearing "
    - interrupt site's debug_text starts with "'called to attack. clearing "

  starts-with() picks only the main scan-clear branch.

  Feature gated by $DABPEnable in DA menu (disabled by default). If the
  hook fires but $DABPEnable is off, DA's BP subsystem silently ignores.

  Diagnostic: after enabling BP scanning in DA menu and completing a
  police scan on a non-player ship, watch script.log for the signal:

    grep "policeassetscannedship" script.log
    grep "MOD: DABP" script.log
-->
<diff>
  <add sel="//do_else[debug_text[starts-with(@text, &quot;'clearing &quot;)]]/do_if[@value='$localtarget.isclass.ship']/do_if[@value='@$localtarget.pilot.$haltedby == this.assignedcontrolled']" pos="prepend">
    <do_if value="($localtarget.trueowner != faction.player) and (this.isplayerowned)">
      <signal_objects object="player.entity" param="'policeassetscannedship'" param2="$localtarget" param3="this.ship"/>
    </do_if>
  </add>
</diff>
